    "body": "(Related)\r\n\r\nI use next script to wrap truffle in a containerized environment:\r\n`https://github.com/earizon/utility_shell_scripts/blob/master/node_wrapper.sh`\r\n\r\nFirst I install in a local directory as:\r\n`$ ./node_wrapper.sh npm install -g --prefix=/root/truffle_install truffle`\r\n\r\nThen on the working directory I create a second utility script (just to save some typing):\r\n\r\n    $ cat truffle.sh \r\n    #!/bin/bash\r\n    ./node_wrapper.sh /root/truffle_install/bin/truffle $*\r\n\r\nFinally I just execute `./truffle.sh <command>` instead of just `truffle <command>`\r\n\r\nThe node_wrapper.sh is really simple. The node version can be changed by just modifying the value of `NODE_VERSION`. This script can be used as a final utility or as a reference for more elaborate setups\r\n\r\n",
